  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I reset my Gmail Password?",
  "response": "To reset your Gmail password, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Gmail Sign-In Page:**\n   - Open your web browser and navigate to the Gmail sign-in page.\n\n2. **Click on \"Forgot Password\":**\n   - On the sign-in page, below the password field, you'll see a link that says \"Forgot password?\" Click on it.\n\n3. **Enter Your Email Address:**\n   - You'll be prompted to enter the email address associated with your Gmail account. Type it in and click \"Next.\"\n\n4. **Verify Your Identity:**\n   - Google will ask you to verify your identity. You may be prompted to enter the last password you remember or answer security questions. If you have two-factor authentication set up, you might need to enter a code sent to your recovery phone or email.\n\n5. **Choose a New Password:**\n   - Once your identity is verified, you'll be prompted to create a new password. Enter your new password and confirm it. Make sure it's strong and secure.\n\n6. **Sign In with Your New Password:**\n   - After setting your new password, you can sign in to your Gmail account using it.\n\n**Additional Tips:**\n- **Recovery Information:** Make sure your recovery email and phone number are up to date. This can make the recovery process much smoother.\n- **Password Strength:** Use a combination of letters, numbers, and symbols to create a strong password.\n- **Two-Factor Authentication:** Consider enabling two-factor authentication for added security.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during this process, you can visit the Google Account Help page for more detailed instructions and troubleshooting.",
